<HEADLINE> Cambodia Sticks to 'One China' Policy: Chea Sim </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Chea Sim, Acting Head of
State and President of Cambodia's Senate, Monday here reaffirmed
that "The Government and Senate of the Kingdom of Cambodia always
uphold 'One China' Policy".
</P>
<P>
The President made the announcement at Chamkar Morn Palace this
morning when he received the credentials from Ning Fukui, newly-
appointed Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the
People's Republic of China to the Kingdom of Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
Samdech Chea Sim said he believes that Ambassador Ning can
accomplish his mission during his term of office, and will make
new contributions to the promotion of the friendship and
cooperation between the two nations. He also expressed thanks for
the good treatment for King Norodom Sihanouk's disease to the
Chinese Government and people.
</P>
<P>
Chinese ambassador Ning said the friendship between China and
Cambodia will be beneficial to peace and stability in the Asian-
Pacific area. He conveyed to Samdech Chea Sim greetings from
President Jiang Zemin, Chairman of the National People's Congress
Standing Committee Li Peng and Chairman of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference Li Ruihuan. 
</P>
